hackathon-description-text: Trying to turn that one idea you have into a finished product? Looking to gain experience working with a team on a large scale coding project? Well, look no further! Come be a part of UCSD's PROM (Project of the Month), hosted by the Computer Science and Engineering Society! This isn't you're average high school prom, this is the real deal.
hackathon-eligibility: Teams can be a maximum of 4 students, and must be composed of all UCSD students.
hackathon-requirements: Anything goes! May the best project win :)
hackathon-rules:
1. Teams can be up to a maximum of 4 UCSD Students
2. All submissions must follow the provided [PROM]pt of the month, and cannot be work pre-prepared before the [PROMP]pt unveiling
3. Products must not contain racist, sexist, or other derogatory/offensive material, and must follow all public laws
4. The work submitted must be a product developed by the members of the team submitting them
5. Teams may not steal or copy the work of another team or private entity
6. Have fun and make something cool :)
hackathon-location-google-maps: https://maps.google.com/?q=9500 Gilman Dr, La Jolla, CA 92093, USA

hackathon-judging-criteria.judging-criterion: Is your idea a creative and innovation solution to a problem?
How did you go about executing your idea? Does the actual product match the idea, and to what degree?
How have you presented your idea? Is it clear what you are working on and why it is a useful product?

hackathon-location-address: 9500 Gilman Dr, La Jolla, CA 92093, USA
hackathon-description-header: Jump start your project with CSES's monthly innovation hackathon!
